Misty's is known for their prime rib. However, Omaha used to have numerous steak houses which were owned by Italian families. They have closed because their children did not want to continue working in the business. Chicago does have some wonderful steak houses. Valentino's became a chain in the mid-70's. It is good, but it does not come close to the original Val's. On Sunday, there would be a line to get in over one block long.
